com.i2group.apollo.commandservice.transport

Class SetItemPrimaryProperties

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.i2group.apollo.commandservice.transport.Command
      • com.i2group.apollo.commandservice.transport.SetItemPrimaryProperties
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ICommand

    public final class SetItemPrimaryProperties
extends Command
implements ICommand
    The ICommand for changing the primary Propertys on an Item.

    If the specified Item already has a primary Property with the same PropertyType as a specified PrimaryPropertyIdentifier, then the existing setting is overwritten.

    If the specified PrimaryPropertyIdentifiers do not include an entry for a particular PropertyType, then the existing setting for that PropertyType is unchanged.

    Leasing:

    • An active lease must exist on the Item whose primary Propertys are to be set.
    Authorization:
    • The current user must have the SecurityAccessLevel.UPDATE access level for the Item having its primary Propertys set.
    Validation:
    • The specified Item must not already be marked as deleted.
    • The specified Item must not have been the source in a merge operation.
    • The specified Item must not have ProhibitedEdit associated with its ItemType.
    • Each specified PrimaryPropertyIdentifier must contain a PropertyType identifier that corresponds to a legal PropertyType for the specified Item.
    • Each specified PrimaryPropertyIdentifier must contain a PropertyType identifier that corresponds to the type of the identified Property.
    • Every specified PrimaryPropertyIdentifier must contain a different PropertyType identifier.
    Since:
    4.0
